laboratory_examinations.findings: The appendix is hyperemic with a thickened wall, fluid-filled, and distended to a maximal diameter of 1.2 cm. Significant periappendiceal fat stranding. An appendicolith is noted. No drainable extraluminal collection or extraluminal air.
Potassium level of 3.7 mEq/L, which is within normal range (3.3 - 5.1 mEq/L).
